WEBVTT

01:08.300 --> 01:12.521
Captions made possible by
HOME BOX OFFICE

01:12.530 --> 01:16.728
A Division of TIME WARNER
ENTERTAINMENT COMPANY, LP.

02:40.600 --> 02:43.296
SO, I SAY TO THIS GUY,
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING

02:43.300 --> 02:45.495
UNLESS YOU GIVE ME
AN ORDER NUMBER.

02:45.500 --> 02:47.195
AND I DON'T APPRECIATE
YOU TAKING THAT

02:47.200 --> 02:48.428
TONE OF VOICE WITH ME.

02:48.430 --> 02:50.898
HE SAYS HE DOESN'T
HAVE AN ORDER NUMBER.

02:50.900 --> 02:53.391
AND I SAY, "WELL, YOU SHOULD
ALWAYS WRITE DOWN

02:53.400 --> 02:54.549
THE ORDER NUMBER."

02:54.560 --> 02:55.822
THEN HE GETS
ALL PISSY.

02:55.830 --> 02:58.890
SAYS HE WANTS TO SPEAK TO
THE PERSON HE ORDERED

02:58.900 --> 03:01.027
THE ASTORIA FLOOR LAMP
FROM AND I SAY,

03:01.030 --> 03:04.124
"WELL, DO YOU
REMEMBER HIS OR HER--"

03:04.130 --> 03:06.690
RIGHT, "NAME ?"

03:06.700 --> 03:08.793
AND HE SAYS,
"OF COURSE NOT".

03:08.800 --> 03:11.758
AND I SAY, "THEN I'M SORRY,
I CAN'T HELP YOU."

03:11.760 --> 03:14.820
THEN HE TELLS ME
THIS ISN'T THE FIRST TIME

03:14.830 --> 03:16.525
HE HAD A PROBLEM
ORDERING FROM US.

03:16.530 --> 03:18.395
LAST CHRISTMAS
HE BOUGHT A CD HOLDER

03:18.400 --> 03:19.799
AND IT ARRIVED
ALL BROKEN,

03:19.800 --> 03:21.597
BUT WHEN WE TOLD HIM
TO SEND IT BACK,

03:21.600 --> 03:25.127
HE COULDN'T BECAUSE HE'D
THROWN AWAY THE BOX IT CAME IN.

03:27.260 --> 03:29.797
SO, I SAY,
"BOO-HOO, MISTER.

03:29.800 --> 03:31.119
AIN'T YOU
GOT IT BAD."

03:31.130 --> 03:33.598
AND HE SAYS, "I WANT TO
TALK TO YOUR SUPERVISOR."

03:36.500 --> 03:39.298
BUT UNFORTUNATELY
HIS HOURS ARE ONLY 8:30--"

04:06.560 --> 04:08.619
ACCORDING TO THE COUSIN
WHO ARRANGED THE FUNERAL.

04:08.630 --> 04:10.951
I BET HE WAS
ABUSING HER.

04:10.960 --> 04:14.555
OR MAYBE HE HAD SOME SICK
SEXUAL THING HE MADE HER DO.

04:14.560 --> 04:15.652
PLEASE STOP.

04:15.660 --> 04:17.423
AND YOU'RE WRONG.

04:17.430 --> 04:20.524
ALL SHE TOLD THE POLICE
WAS THAT HE WAS BORING.

04:22.030 --> 04:24.396
THAT'S IT,
THAT'S ALL SHE SAID ?

04:26.600 --> 04:28.818
THE SICK PART IS,
I UNDERSTAND IT.

04:28.830 --> 04:30.627
I DO TOO.

04:33.960 --> 04:35.894
SOMETIMES
I'M BORING.

04:35.900 --> 04:37.197
I AM TOO.

04:38.930 --> 04:41.649
SO, I SHOULD PROBABLY
BE AT BOTH INTAKES
WITH YOU THIS MORNING,

04:41.660 --> 04:44.493
BUT YOU'LL HAVE TO DO
THE CASKET MEETING
PEOPLE YOURSELF

04:44.500 --> 04:46.252
BECAUSE I'M REALLY
BACKED UP DOWN HERE.

04:46.260 --> 04:47.659
DAVID, MAYBE
WE NEED TO

04:47.660 --> 04:51.323
THINK ABOUT FINDING
A REPLACEMENT FOR RICO.

04:51.330 --> 04:53.525
WHY ? WE'RE DOING
JUST FINE WITHOUT HIM.

04:53.530 --> 04:56.192
IT'S SAVING MONEY,
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

04:58.130 --> 05:00.519
IS THERE SOMETHING YOU'D
LIKE TO SAY ABOUT MY WORK ?

05:00.530 --> 05:03.795
YOU DO A GREAT JOB WHEN
IT COMES TO THE PEOPLE

05:03.800 --> 05:05.722
WHO'VE HAD NICE,
PEACEFUL FAREWELLS.

05:05.730 --> 05:07.425
BUT THE BIG RECONSTRUCT IONS,
COME ON, DAVID,

05:07.430 --> 05:08.454
YOU'RE A LITTLE
OUT OF YOUR LEAGUE.

05:08.460 --> 05:10.348
I SEE, SO, THOSE WHO
CAN'T DO, CRITICIZE.

05:10.360 --> 05:12.499
WE'VE GOT A BODY IN THERE
THAT'S A PAGE ONE REWRITE.

05:12.500 --> 05:15.526
WE'VE GOT TWO MORE
COMING IN TODAY FROM THAT
NIGHTCLUB FIRE IN VALENCIA.

05:15.530 --> 05:16.827
HOW BAD WAS
THAT FIRE ?

05:16.830 --> 05:18.195
WELL, THIS IS WHERE
THEY ENDED UP.

05:18.200 --> 05:19.952
WELL, MAYBE
THE FAMILIES WANT--

05:19.960 --> 05:22.292
OPEN CASKETS, THEY ALREADY
PUT IN THE REQUESTS.

05:22.300 --> 05:25.258
I'LL PUT AN AD
IN THE PAPER TODAY.

05:25.260 --> 05:26.693
IT'S ALREADY
TAKEN CARE OF.

05:26.700 --> 05:28.588
I'VE SCHEDULED SOME INTERVIEWS
FOR THIS AFTERNOON.

05:32.830 --> 05:34.354
AS YOU CAN SEE
FROM MY RESUME,

05:34.360 --> 05:36.692
I'VE HAD THE
GOOD FORTUNE TO STUDY

05:36.700 --> 05:38.725
UNDER A VARIETY OF GIFI'ED
RESTORATIVE ARTISTS.

05:38.730 --> 05:40.197
OH, YOU WORKED OVER
AT HOPE VALLEY.

05:40.200 --> 05:42.020
I'VE KNOWN P.T.
FOR YEARS.

05:42.030 --> 05:43.691
OH.

05:43.700 --> 05:47.124
LOOK, THAT LAWSUIT
ABOUT THE UN-EMBALMED ARM

05:47.130 --> 05:48.722
WAS NOT MY FAULT.

05:48.730 --> 05:50.948
I TOOK THE FALL FOR SOME BITCH
THAT WAS SUPPOSED TO

05:50.960 --> 05:53.997
COVER MY ASS
FOR LEAVING EARLY.

05:54.600 --> 05:57.057
SOMETIMES I WAKE UP
WITH A FEELING OF PANIC,

05:57.060 --> 05:59.392
LIKE MY HEART'S GONNA
BEAT RIGHT OUTI'A MY CHEST.

05:59.400 --> 06:01.220
YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

06:01.230 --> 06:03.152
BUT AFTER I SPEND
A FEW EXTRA HOURS IN BED

06:03.160 --> 06:04.525
AND DO
MY CHANTING,

06:04.530 --> 06:06.953
THE DARK TIME
USUALLY PASSES.

06:08.200 --> 06:09.553
I KNOW IT
SOUNDS FUNNY,

06:09.560 --> 06:12.120
BUT THE FIRST TIME
I EMBALMED SOMEONE,

06:12.130 --> 06:13.791
IT FELT LIKE I WAS
COMING HOME.

06:13.800 --> 06:17.554
I JUST KNEW THAT THIS IS
WHAT I WAS MEANT TO DO.

06:17.560 --> 06:19.323
THAT DOESN'T SOUND
FUNNY AT ALL.

06:19.330 --> 06:21.651
THERE'S SOMETHING VERY
INTIMATE ABOUT IT.

06:21.660 --> 06:23.548
I'M THE LAST
PERSON ON EARTH

06:23.560 --> 06:26.028
WHO GETS TO KNOW
THESE PEOPLE.

06:27.900 --> 06:31.791
ANYWAY, I GUESS I TAKE
WHAT I DO VERY SERIOUSLY.

06:31.800 --> 06:34.394
WELL, I HAVE NO
FURTHER QUESTIONS.

06:34.400 --> 06:35.651
ME, NEITHER.

06:35.660 --> 06:37.525
THANKS FOR
COMING IN, ANGELA.

06:37.530 --> 06:38.349
WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

06:38.360 --> 06:39.918
GREAT.

06:42.530 --> 06:44.293
OH.

06:44.300 --> 06:45.927
IT WAS VERY NICE
TO MEET YOU.

06:45.930 --> 06:47.329
IT WAS NICE
TO MEET YOU.

06:47.330 --> 06:48.319
YEAH.

06:48.330 --> 06:49.752
OKAY.

06:52.500 --> 06:54.593
I'LL WAIT AN HOUR
BEFORE I CALL HER.

06:54.600 --> 06:55.999
WE DON'T WANT TO
LOOK DESPERATE.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.958
JUST FIND OUT IF
SHE CAN START TOMORROW.

07:07.560 --> 07:14.625
I'VE GOT A LOT
OF LIVIN' TO DO

07:14.630 --> 07:16.757
I'M GONNA BREAK OUT,
GONNA GO WILD

07:16.760 --> 07:18.022
HAVE MY WAY

07:18.030 --> 07:23.229
I MAY BREAK
A HEART A DAY

07:24.160 --> 07:25.718
LIFE'S A BALL

07:25.730 --> 07:27.755
IF ONLY YOU KNOW IT

07:27.760 --> 07:32.424
AND IT'S ALL
JUST WAITING FOR YOU

07:33.600 --> 07:35.352
YOU'RE ALIVE

07:35.360 --> 07:37.419
SO, COME ON
AND SHOW IT

07:37.430 --> 07:38.590
( Ruth )
DAVID !

07:38.600 --> 07:41.228
DAVID !

07:43.100 --> 07:44.727
WHY ARE YOU STANDING
THERE LIKE THAT ?

07:50.330 --> 07:52.491
ISN'T A PERSON
ALLOWED TO THINK ?

08:07.630 --> 08:10.292
YOU'RE GONNA WISH
YOU'D GOTI'EN HIGH WITH ME.

08:10.300 --> 08:12.052
I TOLD YOU, I'M NEVER
GE'I'I'ING HIGH AGAIN.

08:12.060 --> 08:14.392
OH, DOESN'T BILLY
LOOK GREAT ?

08:14.400 --> 08:17.096
SO HANDSOME
AND CONFIDENT.

08:17.100 --> 08:19.557
YO, BILLY !

08:21.030 --> 08:22.395
WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR ONE MOMENT ?

08:22.400 --> 08:23.822
THANK YOU GUYS
SO MUCH FOR COMING.

08:23.830 --> 08:25.127
I REALLY
APPRECIATE IT.

08:25.130 --> 08:26.688
THANK GOD
YOU'RE HERE, BRENDA.

08:26.700 --> 08:28.292
MY MOUTH IS REALLY DRY
AND IS MY BREATH BAD ?

08:28.300 --> 08:29.824
IT'S FINE.

08:29.830 --> 08:32.151
OKAY, SO TRUTH,
IS THIS SHOW ANY GOOD ?

08:32.160 --> 08:33.696
OR IS IT JUST
PRETENTIOUS BULLSHIT ?

08:33.700 --> 08:35.656
THERE ARE SO MANY PEOPLE,
IT'S HARD TO SEE THE PICTURES.

08:35.660 --> 08:37.821
THIS IS BILLY'S
BEST WORK EVER.

08:37.830 --> 08:39.195
VERY DISTURBING.

08:39.200 --> 08:40.258
REALLY ?

08:40.260 --> 08:43.058
IAM SO PROUD
OF YOU, GOD !

08:45.730 --> 08:47.618
WHY IS MY
MOTHER HERE ?

08:47.630 --> 08:49.598
OH, GOD.

08:49.600 --> 08:52.319
I INVITED HER AS PART OF
MY ONGOING CAMPAIGN

08:52.330 --> 08:53.888
TO GET HER
TO LIKE ME.

08:53.900 --> 08:55.959
I DIDN'T THINK
SHE'D ACTUALLY TURN UP.

08:59.130 --> 09:01.655
SOME STRANGER JUST
RUBBED MY ASS.

09:01.660 --> 09:04.322
ISN'T THIS
FABULOUS ?

09:04.330 --> 09:07.049
OH, BILLY,
DARLING !

09:11.000 --> 09:12.797
THAN KS, MOM.

09:14.160 --> 09:17.823
YOU CAN'T KEEP HIM
TO YOURSELF ALL THE TIME.

09:21.100 --> 09:22.920
OKAY, NO OFFENSE.

09:22.930 --> 09:25.091
BUT YOUR FAMILY IS FUCKED UP
BEYOND COMPREHENSION.

09:25.100 --> 09:26.727
SHE IS COMPLETELY
TANKED.

09:26.730 --> 09:29.699
I BROUGHT SOMEONE,
I HOPE THAT'S OKAY.

09:29.700 --> 09:30.951
HEY, NIKOLAI.

09:30.960 --> 09:32.496
HELLO, NATE,
HOW ARE YOU ?

09:32.500 --> 09:33.524
THIS IS BRENDA.

09:33.530 --> 09:34.656
GOOD EVENING.

09:34.660 --> 09:36.127
HELLO, DEAR.

09:36.130 --> 09:38.553
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU,
MRS. FISHER.

09:38.560 --> 09:39.891
WHERE'S HIRAM ?

09:39.900 --> 09:42.619
HE'S VISITING HIS SON
IN PORTLAND.

09:43.360 --> 09:44.657
I'M SERIOUS,
DARLING.

09:44.660 --> 09:46.924
THIS NEW STUFF
IS REALLY...

09:46.930 --> 09:47.999
VISCERAL.

09:48.000 --> 09:49.956
NOT AT ALL LEFT-BRAINED
LIKE YOUR FATHER.

09:49.960 --> 09:51.598
YEAH.

09:51.600 --> 09:53.090
HEY, SO,
WHERE IS DAD ?

09:53.100 --> 09:56.456
OH, HONEY, BERN
SENDS HIS REGRETS.

09:56.460 --> 09:58.121
HE'S JUST HEARTSICK.

09:58.130 --> 10:01.190
UNFORTUNATELY HE'S TREATING
ONE OF HIS PATIENTS

10:01.200 --> 10:04.829
WHO'S UNDERGOING A COMPLETE
PSYCHOTIC BREAK AT THE MOMENT.

10:06.100 --> 10:07.795
GEE, THAT ALWAYS
SEEMS TO HAPPEN

10:07.800 --> 10:09.358
WHENEVER THERE'S SOMETHING
IMPORTANT IN MY LIFE.

10:09.360 --> 10:11.419
I GUESS THAT'S JUST
TYPICAL BERNARD--

10:11.430 --> 10:13.455
EXCUSE ME, BURR-NURD
CHENOWITH BEHAVIOR.

10:13.460 --> 10:15.894
PRETENTIOUS DICK.

10:15.900 --> 10:17.959
NOW, YOU JUST HUSH.

10:19.830 --> 10:21.593
I THOUGHT THIS WOULD
BE PAINTINGS.

10:21.600 --> 10:23.227
I COULD TAKE
PHOTOGRAPHS.

10:23.230 --> 10:25.357
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THEY'D BE ANY GOOD.

10:25.360 --> 10:29.649
MRS. FISHER, I'VE NEVER SEEN
YOU HAVING THIS MUCH FUN.

10:31.060 --> 10:32.220
OH, NO, IT'S GREAT.

10:32.230 --> 10:35.722
IAM HAVING FUN
JUST WATCHING YOU.

10:39.100 --> 10:42.354
HEY, MR. SEA'I'I'LE
CO-OP HIPPIE BOY.

10:44.300 --> 10:46.951
OH, MARGARET CHENOWITH,
WHO ARE YOU ?

10:46.960 --> 10:48.723
RUTH FISHER.

10:48.730 --> 10:50.152
NATE'S MOTHER.

10:50.160 --> 10:52.754
THAT EXPLAINS WHY YOU'RE
LOOKING AT ME LIKE I JUST TOOK

10:52.760 --> 10:55.058
A GIANT DUMP ON
YOUR FRONT LAWN.

10:55.060 --> 10:56.493
MOM, IF I'D KNOWN YOU WERE
PU'I'I'ING ON A SHOW TONIGHT,

10:56.500 --> 10:58.923
I WOULD HAVE BOUGHT TICKETS
FOR ALL MY FRIENDS.

10:58.930 --> 11:01.421
GOODY, THERE'S
DR. FEINBERG.

11:01.430 --> 11:04.092
WHAT IS HE
DOING HERE ?

11:04.100 --> 11:06.125
I INVITED HIM.

11:06.130 --> 11:07.757
GARETH FEINBERG, THE GUY
WHO WROTE THE BOOK ?

11:07.760 --> 11:08.852
YEAH.

11:08.860 --> 11:11.055
HE WROTE "CHARLOTTE FUCKING
LIGHT AND DARK".

11:11.060 --> 11:14.359
HE'S A FUCKING EVIL DEAD FISH
OF A FUCKING NAZI FUCK.

11:14.360 --> 11:15.759
DARLING.

11:15.760 --> 11:17.557
TRY NOT TO ACT
SO ADOLESCENT.

11:17.560 --> 11:19.096
IT ONLY MAKES
YOU LOOK BAD.

11:19.100 --> 11:20.328
AS OPPOSED TO BEING
DRUNK IN PUBLIC

11:20.330 --> 11:21.592
AND SLOBBERING
ALL OVER MY BOYFRIEND

11:21.600 --> 11:23.852
WHO, BY THE WAY,
IS COMPLETELY NOT INTERESTED.

11:23.860 --> 11:25.498
ISN'T THIS FUN ?

11:25.500 --> 11:28.526
BILLY, BILLY, BILLY.

11:28.530 --> 11:31.055
IT'S QUITE
POWERFUL STUFF.

11:31.060 --> 11:33.028
IT'S POTENT.

11:33.030 --> 11:34.327
( laughing )

11:34.330 --> 11:37.197
THAT'S A WORD DR. FEINBERG
LIKES TO USE A LOT.

11:37.200 --> 11:41.296
BRENDA, I SEE A LOT OF YOU
IN THESE PHOTOGRAPHS.

11:41.300 --> 11:43.951
HELLO, GARETH.

11:45.030 --> 11:46.019
MARGARET.

11:46.030 --> 11:47.395
EW.

11:49.630 --> 11:51.154
DOES THIS HAVE
A THEME, DARLING ?

11:51.160 --> 11:53.151
I KNOW YOU LIKE YOUR THINGS
TO HAVE A THEME, DON'T YOU ?

11:53.160 --> 11:55.025
MOTHER, NOTHING IS MORE
TEDIOUS THAN WHEN YOU

11:55.030 --> 11:56.725
LOOK FOR MEANING
IN MY WORK.

11:56.730 --> 11:59.051
I DON'T NEED YOUR
FUCKING APPROVAL.

12:02.800 --> 12:04.256
EXCUSE ME.

12:07.500 --> 12:08.626
